# UDS Release Workflow

## Context

The Urban Design System (UDS) spans two Figma files and a documentation site:

- **UDS Tokens** -- Figma file key: `iqKgR73ubUHpQTIcF7XGMy`
- **UDS Components** -- Figma file key: `1XJoUJgtNpw4R0IIT3VjoK`
- **Doc site** -- `uds-docs/` directory, version tracked in `app.js` as `UDS_VERSION`

Both Figma files contain a page named `UDS Version: X.Y` (e.g., `UDS Version: 0.1`).

## Delegated Figma workflows

This rule orchestrates releases. It does NOT contain the full operational
details for Figma reads/imports/writes. Use the focused Figma workflow
artifacts instead:

| Task | Use |
|---|---|
| Prove Figma API/tool capability | `figma-capability-check` agent |
| Read file versions/pages/statuses | `figma-inventory` agent |
| Audit tokens | `figma-token-audit` agent |
| Import tokens | `import-figma-tokens` skill |
| Deep-inspect one component | `figma-component-inspector` agent |
| Sync component status | `sync-figma-component-status` skill |
| Sync component spec from Figma | `sync-figma-component-spec` skill |
| Populate `figmaNodeId` fields | `link-figma-nodes` skill |
| Rebuild Figma release notes | `sync-figma-release-notes` skill |
| One-shot update from Figma | `uds-updated` skill |

Figma token reads must follow `uds-token-architecture.mdc`.
Figma component reads must follow `uds-figma-component-inspection.mdc`.
Figma writes must follow `uds-figma-write-safety.mdc`.
All findings must follow `uds-figma-change-classification.mdc`.

## Version Detection

Whenever you interact with either UDS Figma file (reading components, inspecting tokens, importing assets), you MUST:

1. Run the `uds-figma-preflight.mdc` checks.
2. List pages in the file via Figma tooling, apply the `{Ignore}` page filter
   from `uds-figma-preflight.mdc`, and find the page matching `UDS Version: *`.
3. Parse the version number from the page name.
4. Read `UDS_VERSION` from `uds-docs/docs/app.js`.
5. If the Figma version is higher than the site version, alert the user and begin the Release Questionnaire below.

Do NOT silently skip this check. If you detect a mismatch, pause your current task and address it first.

## Release Questionnaire

When a version bump is detected, present questions in rounds using the AskQuestion tool.

### Round 1 -- What Changed

- "I noticed UDS went from {old} to {new} in Figma. What's in this release?"
- "Are there any breaking changes? (renamed tokens, removed classes, changed markup)"
- Auto-detect component status changes by reading page name prefixes (stoplight icons) from UDS Components and comparing against each `uds/components/<id>/status.json`. Report any mismatches.

### Round 2 -- Tokens

Run `figma-token-audit` first. Direct Figma Variables reads are the
primary source; token ZIP exports are fallback only when direct variable
access is unavailable, partial, or cannot produce the normalized token
model required by `uds-token-architecture.mdc`.

The audit must report:
- direct variable read status (success / partial / failed)
- collection and mode structure diff
- added tokens
- removed / renamed / moved token candidates
- value changes across modes
- alias target changes
- import recommendation

Only request ZIPs if the token audit explicitly says fallback is required.

### Round 3 -- New Components

- Run `figma-inventory` to compare Figma component pages (those with stoplight prefixes, excluding pages whose names contain `{Ignore}`) against `uds/components.json`, sidebar links, and per-component `uds/components/<id>/spec.json`.
- The inventory must include component-set variant coverage for every
  non-ignored component page: component-set names, variant-property names,
  property values, and variant counts.
- For changed/new components, run `figma-component-inspector`. Do not rely on screenshots alone.
- Report any components that exist in Figma but not the site.
- "Any components deprecated or removed?"

### Round 4 -- Release Prep

- "Should I run release.sh to snapshot v{old} and bump the site to v{new}?"
- "Should I update the release notes pages in both Figma files?"
- "Anything else to note for the changelog or migration guide?"

## Automated Release Steps

After the questionnaire, execute these steps in order. NEVER run `release.sh` without explicit user confirmation.

1. **Snapshot**: Run `bash uds-docs/release.sh {new_version}` to archive the current `uds/` into `versions/{old}/uds/` (UDS-only, not full-site).
2. **Update statuses**: Run `sync-figma-component-status` and update each affected component's `uds/components/<id>/status.json` only for high-confidence, non-breaking status changes. Do NOT touch the legacy `COMPONENT_STATUS` table — it's gone (Phase 13b). The boot loader builds the in-memory map from `uds/components/<id>/status.json` files via `uds/components.json`.
3. **Update CHANGELOG**: Add per-component changelog entries to `uds/components/<id>/changelog.json` (each component owns its own history). For non-component release notes, add to `uds/CHANGELOG.globalNotes.json` under the new version key. Then run `bash scripts/aggregate-changelog.sh` to refresh `uds/CHANGELOG.json`.
   - Use correct `type`: `added`, `changed`, `fixed`, `deprecated`, `removed`
   - Do not write the release entry from page names alone. It must include the
     component-set variant coverage pass from `figma-inventory`, including
     meaningful new/confirmed variant and state coverage on existing
     components and internal/support pages intentionally excluded from public
     docs.
4. **Regenerate tokens**: Run `import-figma-tokens`; direct Figma Variables are primary, ZIPs fallback only. After regen, run `bash scripts/audit-theme-contrast.sh` to verify the 6-theme WCAG AA contract still holds. If new tokens regress contrast, document with token bumps in the same PR.
5. **Add new components** (if any): Use `new-component` only after `figma-inventory` / `figma-component-inspector` identify high-confidence new components with enough required minimum content. Then run `bash scripts/aggregate-components.sh` to refresh `uds/components.json`.
6. **Update Figma release notes**: Run `sync-figma-release-notes` to populate the new version page in both UDS Tokens and UDS Components with the unified changelog
7. **Bump site**: Run `bash uds-docs/bump-site.sh` to set the initial SITE build counter
8. **Verify**: Open the browser and confirm changelog, version dropdown, and status badges are correct
   - Verify that the 0.x release changelog includes token changes, new
     components, existing-component variant/state coverage, and excluded
     internal/support pages when applicable
   - Use the version dropdown to switch to the prior version (`?uds={old}`)
     and confirm the archive renders correctly through `udsResolve()`.

## Post-Release Checklist

After all automated steps, print this checklist for the user:

```
Release v{new} complete. Manual Figma steps remaining:
- [ ] Publish library in UDS Tokens (with description: "UDS {new} -- {summary}")
- [ ] Publish library in UDS Components (same description)
- [ ] Save to Version History in both files (Cmd+Opt+S, title: "UDS {new} -- {summary}")
- [ ] Update cover page version text in both files
- [ ] Update component descriptions with @updated {new} tags (for changed components)
```

## Changelog Sync Rule

Whenever a per-component `uds/components/<id>/changelog.json` or `uds/CHANGELOG.globalNotes.json` is modified — whether during a formal release or an ad-hoc update (e.g., adding a new component, fixing an entry, reordering) — you MUST:

1. Run `bash scripts/aggregate-changelog.sh` to refresh the aggregated `uds/CHANGELOG.json`.
2. Update the Release Notes pages in **both** Figma files (`UDS Tokens` and `UDS Components`) to match. The two Figma changelogs must always be identical to each other and to the aggregated site changelog. Use `sync-figma-release-notes` to:
   1. Navigate to the `UDS Version: X.Y` page in each file.
   2. Remove only the existing "Release Notes" frame.
   3. Rebuild it programmatically with the full changelog content (all versions, newest first), using the established styled format.
   4. Verify both files contain identical release-note text.

Never leave Figma changelogs out of sync with the site. If you forget, fix it immediately once noticed.

## Key File References

- `uds-docs/uds/version.json` — single source of truth for current UDS version
- `uds-docs/uds/components.json` — manifest of every component in this release
- `uds-docs/uds/CHANGELOG.json` — aggregated release changelog (auto-built; do NOT edit by hand)
- `uds-docs/uds/CHANGELOG.globalNotes.json` — hand-curated non-component release notes per version
- `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/{spec,status,changelog,impl}.json` — single source of truth for that component
- `uds-docs/docs/app.js` — router, render functions, theme switcher
- `uds-docs/docs/helpers/uds-path.js` — `udsResolve()`, `viewingVersion()` for version-aware fetches
- `uds-docs/index.html` — SPA shell, sidebar nav, `data-page` placeholders
- `uds-docs/release.sh` — snapshots `uds/` to `versions/<old>/uds/`, bumps `uds/version.json`
- `uds-docs/bump-site.sh` — increments SITE build counter and cache-busting params
- `uds-docs/versions.json` — manifest of archived versions (drives the version dropdown)
- `scripts/aggregate-changelog.sh` — regenerates `uds/CHANGELOG.json` from per-component changelogs
- `scripts/aggregate-components.sh` — regenerates `uds/components.json` from `uds/components/<id>/`
- `scripts/audit-theme-contrast.sh` — multi-theme axe-core a11y audit (WCAG AA across 6 themes)

## Component Status Mapping

Figma page name prefixes map to the `current` field in each per-component `status.json`:

| Figma Prefix | Status Key     | Badge Label        |
|-------------|----------------|--------------------|
| (black)     | `placeholder`  | Not Started        |
| (red)       | `blocked`      | Blocked            |
| (orange)    | `in-progress`  | In Progress        |
| (yellow)    | `review`       | In Review          |
| (green)     | `production`   | Production Ready   |
